40struct entry {
41 char *principal;
42 char *key;
43 char *max_life;
44 char *max_renew;
45 char *created;
46 char *modified;
47 char *valid_start;
48 char *valid_end;
49 char *pw_end;
50 char *flags;
51 char *generation;
52 char *extensions;
53};
54
55static char *
56skip_next(char *p)
57{
58 while(*p && !isspace((unsigned char)*p))
59 p++;
60 *p++ = 0;
61 while(*p && isspace((unsigned char)*p))
62 p++;
63 return p;
64}
65
66/*
67 * Parse the time in `s', returning:
68 * -1 if error parsing
69 * 0 if none present
70 * 1 if parsed ok
71 */
72
73static int
74parse_time_string(time_t *t, const char *s)
75{
76 int year, month, date, hour, minute, second;
77 struct tm tm;
78
79 if(strcmp(s, "-") == 0)
80 return 0;
81 if(sscanf(s, "%04d%02d%02d%02d%02d%02d",
82 &year, &month, &date, &hour, &minute, &second) != 6)
83 return -1;
84 tm.tm_year = year - 1900;
85 tm.tm_mon = month - 1;
86 tm.tm_mday = date;
87 tm.tm_hour = hour;
88 tm.tm_min = minute;
89 tm.tm_sec = second;
90 tm.tm_isdst = 0;
91 *t = timegm(&tm);
92 return 1;
93}
94
95/*
96 * parse time, allocating space in *t if it's there
97 */
98
99static int
100parse_time_string_alloc (time_t **t, const char *s)
101{
102 time_t tmp;
103 int ret;
104
105 *t = NULL;
106 ret = parse_time_string (&tmp, s);
107 if (ret == 1) {
108 *t = malloc (sizeof (**t));
109 if (*t == NULL)
110 krb5_errx (context, 1, "malloc: out of memory");
111 **t = tmp;
112 }
113 return ret;
114}
115
116/*
117 * see parse_time_string for calling convention
118 */
119
120static int
121parse_integer(unsigned int *u, const char *s)
122{
123 if(strcmp(s, "-") == 0)
124 return 0;
125 if (sscanf(s, "%u", u) != 1)
126 return -1;
127 return 1;
128}
129
130static int
131parse_integer_alloc (unsigned int **u, const char *s)
132{
133 unsigned int tmp;
134 int ret;
135
136 *u = NULL;
137 ret = parse_integer (&tmp, s);
138 if (ret == 1) {
139 *u = malloc (sizeof (**u));
140 if (*u == NULL)
141 krb5_errx (context, 1, "malloc: out of memory");
142 **u = tmp;
143 }
144 return ret;
145}

147/*
148 * Parse dumped keys in `str' and store them in `ent'
149 * return -1 if parsing failed
150 */
151
152static int
153parse_keys(hdb_entry *ent, char *str)
154{
155 krb5_error_code ret;
156 int tmp;
157 char *p;
158 size_t i;
159
160 p = strsep(&str, ":");
161 if (sscanf(p, "%d", &tmp) != 1)
162 return 1;
163 ent->kvno = tmp;
164 p = strsep(&str, ":");
165 while(p){
166 Key *key;
167 key = realloc(ent->keys.val,
168 (ent->keys.len + 1) * sizeof(*ent->keys.val));
169 if(key == NULL)
170 krb5_errx (context, 1, "realloc: out of memory");
171 ent->keys.val = key;
172 key = ent->keys.val + ent->keys.len;
173 ent->keys.len++;
174 memset(key, 0, sizeof(*key));
175 if(sscanf(p, "%d", &tmp) == 1) {
176 key->mkvno = malloc(sizeof(*key->mkvno));
177 *key->mkvno = tmp;
178 } else
179 key->mkvno = NULL;
180 p = strsep(&str, ":");
181 if (sscanf(p, "%d", &tmp) != 1)
182 return 1;
183 key->key.keytype = tmp;
184 p = strsep(&str, ":");
185 ret = krb5_data_alloc(&key->key.keyvalue, (strlen(p) - 1) / 2 + 1);
186 if (ret)
187 krb5_err (context, 1, ret, "krb5_data_alloc");
188 for(i = 0; i < strlen(p); i += 2) {
189 if(sscanf(p + i, "%02x", &tmp) != 1)
190 return 1;
191 ((u_char*)key->key.keyvalue.data)[i / 2] = tmp;
192 }
193 p = strsep(&str, ":");
194 if(strcmp(p, "-") != 0){
195 unsigned type;
196 size_t p_len;
197
198 if(sscanf(p, "%u/", &type) != 1)
199 return 1;
200 p = strchr(p, '/');
201 if(p == NULL)
202 return 1;
203 p++;
204 p_len = strlen(p);
205
206 key->salt = calloc(1, sizeof(*key->salt));
207 if (key->salt == NULL)
208 krb5_errx (context, 1, "malloc: out of memory");
209 key->salt->type = type;
210
211 if (p_len) {
212 if(*p == '\"') {
213 ret = krb5_data_copy(&key->salt->salt, p + 1, p_len - 2);
214 if (ret)
215 krb5_err (context, 1, ret, "krb5_data_copy");
216 } else {
217 ret = krb5_data_alloc(&key->salt->salt,
218 (p_len - 1) / 2 + 1);
219 if (ret)
220 krb5_err (context, 1, ret, "krb5_data_alloc");
221 for(i = 0; i < p_len; i += 2){
222 if (sscanf(p + i, "%02x", &tmp) != 1)
223 return 1;
224 ((u_char*)key->salt->salt.data)[i / 2] = tmp;
225 }
226 }
227 } else
228 krb5_data_zero (&key->salt->salt);
229 }
230 p = strsep(&str, ":");
231 }
232 return 0;
233}

235/*
236 * see parse_time_string for calling convention
237 */
238
239static int
240parse_event(Event *ev, char *s)
241{
242 krb5_error_code ret;
243 char *p;
244
245 if(strcmp(s, "-") == 0)
246 return 0;
247 memset(ev, 0, sizeof(*ev));
248 p = strsep(&s, ":");
249 if(parse_time_string(&ev->time, p) != 1)
250 return -1;
251 p = strsep(&s, ":");
252 ret = krb5_parse_name(context, p, &ev->principal);
253 if (ret)
254 return -1;
255 return 1;
256}
257
258static int
259parse_event_alloc (Event **ev, char *s)
260{
261 Event tmp;
262 int ret;
263
264 *ev = NULL;
265 ret = parse_event (&tmp, s);
266 if (ret == 1) {
267 *ev = malloc (sizeof (**ev));
268 if (*ev == NULL)
269 krb5_errx (context, 1, "malloc: out of memory");
270 **ev = tmp;
271 }
272 return ret;
273}
274
275static int
276parse_hdbflags2int(HDBFlags *f, const char *s)
277{
278 int ret;
279 unsigned int tmp;
280
281 ret = parse_integer (&tmp, s);
282 if (ret == 1)
283 *f = int2HDBFlags (tmp);
284 return ret;
285}
286
287static int
288parse_generation(char *str, GENERATION **gen)
289{
290 char *p;
291 int v;
292
293 if(strcmp(str, "-") == 0 || *str == '\0') {
294 *gen = NULL;
295 return 0;
296 }
297 *gen = calloc(1, sizeof(**gen));
298
299 p = strsep(&str, ":");
300 if(parse_time_string(&(*gen)->time, p) != 1)
301 return -1;
302 p = strsep(&str, ":");
303 if(sscanf(p, "%d", &v) != 1)
304 return -1;
305 (*gen)->usec = v;
306 p = strsep(&str, ":");
307 if(sscanf(p, "%d", &v) != 1)
308 return -1;
309 (*gen)->gen = v - 1; /* XXX gets bumped in _hdb_store */
310 return 0;
311}
312
313static int
314parse_extensions(char *str, HDB_extensions **e)
315{
316 char *p;
317 int ret;
318
319 if(strcmp(str, "-") == 0 || *str == '\0') {
320 *e = NULL;
321 return 0;
322 }
323 *e = calloc(1, sizeof(**e));
324
325 p = strsep(&str, ":");
326
327 while (p) {
328 HDB_extension ext;
329 ssize_t len;
330 void *d;
331
332 len = strlen(p);
333 d = malloc(len);
334
335 len = hex_decode(p, d, len);
336 if (len < 0) {
337 free(d);
338 return -1;
339 }
340
341 ret = decode_HDB_extension(d, len, &ext, NULL);
342 free(d);
343 if (ret)
344 return -1;
345 d = realloc((*e)->val, ((*e)->len + 1) * sizeof((*e)->val[0]));
346 if (d == NULL)
347 abort();
348 (*e)->val = d;
349 (*e)->val[(*e)->len] = ext;
350 (*e)->len++;
351
352 p = strsep(&str, ":");
353 }
354
355 return 0;
356}

359/*
360 * Parse the dump file in `filename' and create the database (merging
361 * iff merge)
362 */
363
364static int
365doit(const char *filename, int mergep)
366{
367 krb5_error_code ret = 0;
368 FILE *f;
369 char s[8192]; /* XXX should fix this properly */
370 char *p;
371 int line;
372 int flags = O_RDWR;
373 struct entry e;
374 hdb_entry_ex ent;
375 HDB *db = _kadm5_s_get_db(kadm_handle);
376
377 f = fopen(filename, "r");
378 if(f == NULL){
379 krb5_warn(context, errno, "fopen(%s)", filename);
380 return 1;
381 }
382 /*
383 * We don't have a version number in the dump, so we don't know which iprop
384 * log entries to keep, if any. We throw the log away.
385 *
386 * We could merge the ipropd-master/slave dump/load here as an option, in
387 * which case we would first load the dump.
388 *
389 * If we're merging, first recover unconfirmed records in the existing log.
390 */
391 if (mergep)
392 ret = kadm5_log_init(kadm_handle);
393 if (ret == 0)
394 ret = kadm5_log_reinit(kadm_handle, 0);
395 if (ret) {
396 fclose (f);
397 krb5_warn(context, ret, "kadm5_log_reinit");
398 return 1;
399 }
400
401 if(!mergep)
402 flags |= O_CREAT | O_TRUNC;
403 ret = db->hdb_open(context, db, flags, 0600);
404 if(ret){
405 krb5_warn(context, ret, "hdb_open");
406 fclose(f);
407 return 1;
408 }
409 line = 0;
410 ret = 0;
411 while(fgets(s, sizeof(s), f) != NULL) {
412 line++;
413
414 p = s;
415 while (isspace((unsigned char)*p))
416 p++;
417
418 e.principal = p;
419 for(p = s; *p; p++){
420 if(*p == '\\')
421 p++;
422 else if(isspace((unsigned char)*p)) {
423 *p = 0;
424 break;
425 }
426 }
427 p = skip_next(p);
428
429 e.key = p;
430 p = skip_next(p);
431
432 e.created = p;
433 p = skip_next(p);
434
435 e.modified = p;
436 p = skip_next(p);
437
438 e.valid_start = p;
439 p = skip_next(p);
440
441 e.valid_end = p;
442 p = skip_next(p);
443
444 e.pw_end = p;
445 p = skip_next(p);
446
447 e.max_life = p;
448 p = skip_next(p);
449
450 e.max_renew = p;
451 p = skip_next(p);
452
453 e.flags = p;
454 p = skip_next(p);
455
456 e.generation = p;
457 p = skip_next(p);
458
459 e.extensions = p;
460 skip_next(p);
461
462 memset(&ent, 0, sizeof(ent));
463 ret = krb5_parse_name(context, e.principal, &ent.entry.principal);
464 if(ret) {
465 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(context, ret);
466 fprintf(stderr, "%s:%d:%s (%s)\n",
467 filename, line, msg, e.principal);
468 krb5_free_error_message(context, msg);
469 continue;
470 }
471
472 if (parse_keys(&ent.entry, e.key)) {
473 fprintf (stderr, "%s:%d:error parsing keys (%s)\n",
474 filename, line, e.key);
475 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
476 continue;
477 }
478
479 if (parse_event(&ent.entry.created_by, e.created) == -1) {
480 fprintf (stderr, "%s:%d:error parsing created event (%s)\n",
481 filename, line, e.created);
482 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
483 continue;
484 }
485 if (parse_event_alloc (&ent.entry.modified_by, e.modified) == -1) {
486 fprintf (stderr, "%s:%d:error parsing event (%s)\n",
487 filename, line, e.modified);
488 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
489 continue;
490 }
491 if (parse_time_string_alloc (&ent.entry.valid_start, e.valid_start) == -1) {
492 fprintf (stderr, "%s:%d:error parsing time (%s)\n",
493 filename, line, e.valid_start);
494 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
495 continue;
496 }
497 if (parse_time_string_alloc (&ent.entry.valid_end, e.valid_end) == -1) {
498 fprintf (stderr, "%s:%d:error parsing time (%s)\n",
499 filename, line, e.valid_end);
500 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
501 continue;
502 }
503 if (parse_time_string_alloc (&ent.entry.pw_end, e.pw_end) == -1) {
504 fprintf (stderr, "%s:%d:error parsing time (%s)\n",
505 filename, line, e.pw_end);
506 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
507 continue;
508 }
509
510 if (parse_integer_alloc (&ent.entry.max_life, e.max_life) == -1) {
511 fprintf (stderr, "%s:%d:error parsing lifetime (%s)\n",
512 filename, line, e.max_life);
513 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
514 continue;
515
516 }
517 if (parse_integer_alloc (&ent.entry.max_renew, e.max_renew) == -1) {
518 fprintf (stderr, "%s:%d:error parsing lifetime (%s)\n",
519 filename, line, e.max_renew);
520 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
521 continue;
522 }
523
524 if (parse_hdbflags2int (&ent.entry.flags, e.flags) != 1) {
525 fprintf (stderr, "%s:%d:error parsing flags (%s)\n",
526 filename, line, e.flags);
527 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
528 continue;
529 }
530
531 if(parse_generation(e.generation, &ent.entry.generation) == -1) {
532 fprintf (stderr, "%s:%d:error parsing generation (%s)\n",
533 filename, line, e.generation);
534 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
535 continue;
536 }
537
538 if(parse_extensions(e.extensions, &ent.entry.extensions) == -1) {
539 fprintf (stderr, "%s:%d:error parsing extension (%s)\n",
540 filename, line, e.extensions);
541 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
542 continue;
543 }
544
545 ret = db->hdb_store(context, db, HDB_F_REPLACE, &ent);
546 hdb_free_entry (context, &ent);
547 if (ret) {
548 krb5_warn(context, ret, "db_store");
549 break;
550 }
551 }
552 (void) kadm5_log_end(kadm_handle);
553 db->hdb_close(context, db);
554 fclose(f);
555 return ret != 0;
556}
557
558
559extern int local_flag;
560
561static int
562loadit(int mergep, const char *name, int argc, char **argv)
563{
564 if(!local_flag) {
565 krb5_warnx(context, "%s is only available in local (-l) mode", name);
566 return 0;
567 }
568
569 return doit(argv[0], mergep);
570}
571
572int
573load(void *opt, int argc, char **argv)
574{
575 return loadit(0, "load", argc, argv);
576}
577
578int
579merge(void *opt, int argc, char **argv)
580{
581 return loadit(1, "merge", argc, argv);
582}
